    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-24T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="636"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2331/293: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-24T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 24, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>256. Trade agreement negotiations. The Peruvian Embassy has inquired repeatedly
                    regarding Schedule II proposals to be transmitted to Peruvian Government through
                    you. However, our position regarding cotton has not yet been worked out and it
                    may be several days before it can be. Since the list cannot reach you before
                    departure of Dasso and Beltran, it will be presented here following their
                    arrival.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
